<node id="&quot;2004&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">2004 is a year in the global life expectancy data collection period with recorded measurements across numerous countries and regions. Life expectancy values for 2004 vary significantly by geography, ranging from 41.87 years in Eswatini to 82.37 years in Japan. Notable country-specific measurements include China at 71.93 years, India at 65.06 years, the USA at 77.40 years, Canada at 79.85 years, Australia at 80.76 years, and Italy at 80.53 years. Regional aggregates recorded include EUR at 73.32 years and AFR at 54.89 years. Additional countries with documented 2004 life expectancy data include Argentina, Bahrain, Belarus, Cuba, Czechia, Estonia, Ireland, Kazakhstan, Kenya, Kiribati, Latvia, New Zealand, Singapore, Yemen, and the Republic of Korea, among many others across Africa, Asia, Europe, and the Americas. The global life expectancy in 2004 was recorded at approximately 67.95 years, reflecting the wide disparities in health outcomes and life expectancy across different nations and regions during that year.</data>
