<node id="&quot;2012&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">2012 is a year in the global life expectancy data collection period with recorded measurements across numerous countries and regions. Life expectancy values for 2012 vary significantly by country, reflecting differences in healthcare systems, economic development, and living conditions. Notable high life expectancy values include Japan (83.33 years), Switzerland (82.39 years), Australia (82.27 years), Italy (81.84 years), and Iceland (81.98 years). Mid-range values include China (75.48 years), the USA (78.77 years), and the Russian Federation (70.19 years). Lower life expectancy values are recorded in countries such as Lesotho (49.02 years), Eswatini (49.11 years), Somalia (50.11 years), and Chad (56.60 years). Regional aggregates for 2012 show EUR at 76.36 years and AFR at 60.93 years. The global life expectancy for 2012 was recorded at 71.31 years. Additional country-specific measurements include India (68.23 years), Pakistan (64.82 years), Senegal (66.29 years), Mozambique (53.74 years), South Sudan (59.31 years), and numerous others across Africa, Asia, Europe, and the Americas, demonstrating the wide range of life expectancy outcomes globally during this year.</data>
