<node id="&quot;2005&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">2005 is a year in the global life expectancy data collection period with recorded measurements across numerous countries and regions. Life expectancy values for 2005 vary significantly by country, reflecting differences in healthcare, development, and living conditions. Notable high life expectancy values include Switzerland at 81.11 years, Japan at 82.24 years, Italy at 80.51 years, Iceland at 80.90 years, Norway at 80.05 years, and Australia at 80.84 years. Mid-range values include China at 72.44 years, the USA at 77.38 years, Canada at 79.95 years, and Spain at 80.01 years. Lower life expectancy values are recorded in countries such as Eswatini at 41.77 years, Lesotho at 42.66 years, Zimbabwe at 45.71 years, Burundi at 50.91 years, and Mozambique at 51.93 years. Regional aggregates for 2005 include EUR (Europe) at 73.41 years and AFR (Africa) at 55.64 years. The global life expectancy in 2005 was recorded at approximately 68.39 years, representing the average across all measured populations during this year in the data series.</data>
