<node id="&quot;2002&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">2002 is a year in the global life expectancy data collection period with recorded measurements across numerous countries and regions. Life expectancy values for 2002 vary significantly by geography, ranging from lows of 43.64 years in Eswatini to highs of 82.10 years in Japan. Notable country-specific measurements include China at 71.45 years, India at 64.17 years, the USA at 76.85 years, Canada at 79.42 years, Australia at 80.19 years, and the Russian Federation at 64.86 years. Regional aggregates recorded include EUR at 72.71 years and AFR at 53.84 years. Additional documented life expectancy values for 2002 span countries such as Spain (79.49 years), Italy (79.96 years), Switzerland (80.41 years), France (79.14 years), and numerous others across Africa, Asia, Europe, and the Americas, reflecting the comprehensive global health monitoring conducted during this year.</data>
