<node id="&quot;2013&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">2013 is a year in the global life expectancy data collection period, representing the fourteenth year in multiple tracking sequences. During this year, life expectancy measurements were recorded across numerous countries and regions worldwide, with values varying significantly by geographic location and development status.

Specific life expectancy measurements for 2013 include: China at 75.84 years, India at 68.52 years, Japan at 83.56 years, Switzerland at 82.48 years, Italy at 82.29 years, Spain at 82.48 years, Australia at 82.46 years, Iceland at 82.07 years, France at 81.82 years, Canada at 81.56 years, Sweden at 81.64 years, Israel at 81.92 years, New Zealand at 81.36 years, Norway at 81.43 years, Denmark at 80.16 years, Finland at 80.68 years, Slovenia at 80.14 years, USA at 78.76 years, Iran at 77.20 years, Panama at 77.65 years, Nicaragua at 77.26 years, Türkiye at 76.83 years, Tunisia at 76.61 years, Barbados at 76.24 years, Qatar at 75.80 years, Sri Lanka at 75.82 years, North Macedonia at 75.43 years, Romania at 75.00 years, Serbia at 75.22 years, Belize at 74.31 years, Jamaica at 74.22 years, Libya at 74.21 years, Dominican Republic at 73.28 years, Czechia at 78.11 years, Lithuania at 73.87 years, Russian Federation at 70.70 years, Myanmar at 66.44 years, Mongolia at 68.39 years, Bangladesh at 72.59 years, Thailand at 76.54 years, Philippines at 69.45 years, Guatemala at 71.75 years, Paraguay at 75.04 years, Peru at 79.48 years, Honduras at 69.35 years, Haiti at 61.92 years, Iraq at 71.23 years, Pakistan at 65.11 years, Senegal at 66.59 years, Côte d'Ivoire at 59.31 years, Kenya at recorded values, Mozambique at 54.24 years, South Sudan at 59.03 years, Lesotho at 48.96 years, Eswatini at 49.98 years, Somalia at 52.50 years, Chad at 57.01 years, Democratic Republic of the Congo at 58.89 years, Guinea at 59.13 years, Mali at 59.38 years, Burkina Faso at 59.96 years, Burundi at 61.79 years, Liberia at 61.38 years, Gambia at 63.42 years, Equatorial Guinea at 60.97 years, Togo at recorded values, Cambodia at recorded values, Afghanistan at recorded values, and Vietnam marking its fourteenth year in the tracking sequence. Regional aggregates include EUR at 76.70 years and AFR at 61.52 years. The global life expectancy for 2013 was recorded at 71.66 years.</data>
