<node id="&quot;2011&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">2011 is a year in the global life expectancy data collection period, encompassing measurements across numerous countries and regions. The year contains diverse life expectancy values reflecting significant variation in health outcomes worldwide. Notable high values include Switzerland at 82.37 years, Japan at 82.82 years, Italy at 81.83 years, and Australia at 81.93 years. Mid-range values include China at 75.04 years, India at 67.84 years, and the Russian Federation at 69.77 years. Lower values are recorded for countries including Somalia at 43.81 years, Eswatini at 48.07 years, Lesotho at 49.10 years, and Chad at 56.18 years. Regional aggregates show EUR (Europe) at 76.14 years and AFR (Africa) at 60.26 years. The global life expectancy for 2011 was measured at 70.93 years. Additional country-specific measurements include Canada at 81.40 years, New Zealand at 80.75 years, Norway at 80.97 years, France at 81.58 years, and the USA at 78.65 years, among many others spanning all continents and development levels.</data>
