<node id="&quot;2008&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">2008 is a year in the global life expectancy data collection period with recorded measurements across numerous countries and regions. Life expectancy values for 2008 vary significantly by geographic location, ranging from lows of 44.28 years in Eswatini and 45.90 years in Lesotho to highs of 82.83 years in Japan and 81.86 years in Switzerland. Notable recorded values include China at 74.00 years, India at 66.43 years, the USA at 78.05 years, Canada at 80.56 years, and Australia at 81.32 years. Regional measurements show EUR at 74.82 years and AFR at 58.09 years. Additional country-specific measurements for 2008 include Italy (81.37 years), France (80.87 years), Norway (80.49 years), New Zealand (80.31 years), Iceland (81.29 years), and numerous others across Africa, Asia, Europe, and the Americas. The global life expectancy for 2008 was recorded at 69.70 years, representing a comprehensive snapshot of worldwide health outcomes during that year.</data>
