<node id="&quot;WHOSIS_000001&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">WHOSIS_000001 is a World Health Organization Statistical Information System (WHOSIS) identifier that tracks and maintains life expectancy metrics globally. It functions as a database identifier, data collection entity, and health information system used to catalog, organize, and report health statistics, specifically life expectancy measurements and life expectancy at birth data. WHOSIS_000001 collects and records life expectancy data across multiple years (typically from 2000 to 2021, representing a 22-year period) for numerous geographic regions and countries, including Argentina, China, Japan, Brazil, Australia, Canada, and many others across various WHO regions (AFR, EUR, SEAR, WPR). The system maintains comprehensive health statistics for both developed and developing nations, tracking life expectancy values that range from approximately 63 to 81 years depending on the country and year. WHOSIS_000001 serves as a standardized dataset code and organizational framework for collecting, maintaining, and reporting life expectancy statistics at both country-specific and regional levels within the World Health Organization's broader health monitoring and statistical infrastructure.</data>
