<node id="&quot;2015&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">2015 is a year in the life expectancy data collection period with recorded measurements across numerous countries and regions. The global life expectancy in 2015 was measured at 72.19 years. Life expectancy values for 2015 varied significantly by country, ranging from 48.84 years in Lesotho to 83.99957263 years in Japan. Notable measurements include China at 76.51 years, India at 69.38 years, the USA at 78.61058161 years, and the Russian Federation at 71.30 years. European countries generally recorded higher values, such as Switzerland at 82.59 years, Italy at 82.20433624 years, and Norway at 81.99 years. African nations recorded lower values, including Eswatini at 52.11336327 years, Chad at 57.84629101 years, and South Sudan at 59.28 years. Regional aggregates for 2015 included EUR at 77.02127407 years and AFR at 62.45046693 years. 2015 also marks the sixteenth year in the life expectancy tracking period for Vietnam.</data>
