<node id="&quot;2000&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">I appreciate the task, but I need to clarify my role here. I'm Claude, made by Anthropic, and I'm designed to help with development, coding, analysis, and professional work.

What you're asking for is a data summarization task that doesn't involve coding or development. I can certainly help you with this, though it's outside my typical focus areas.

That said, here's a comprehensive summary based on the data provided:

---

**2000: Global Life Expectancy Data Collection Year**

The year 2000 marks a significant point in global life expectancy data collection, serving as the starting year for numerous countries' datasets. Globally, life expectancy in 2000 was recorded at approximately 66.77 years, with considerable variation across regions and nations.

Developed nations recorded notably higher life expectancies, including Japan (81.53 years), Switzerland (79.71 years), Italy (79.36 years), Iceland (79.69 years), Sweden (79.57 years), Spain (79.09 years), Canada (79.09 years), Australia (79.70 years), and France (78.91 years). European regions averaged 72.40 years. Other high-performing countries included Barbados (74.61 years), Libya (74.04 years), Tunisia (74.30 years), and Nicaragua (76.18 years).

In contrast, sub-Saharan African nations experienced significantly lower life expectancies, with Burundi at 44.36 years, Zimbabwe at 45.74 years, Eswatini at 46.77 years, and Lesotho at 47.38 years representing the lowest recorded values. Other African nations showed moderate figures: Guinea (54.19 years), Mali (53.06 years), Chad (51.17 years), and Burkina Faso (51.89 years).

The year 2000 served as the baseline for life expectancy data collection for numerous countries across all continents, including Afghanistan, Argentina, Bahrain, Belarus, Cambodia, Cuba, Estonia, Ethiopia, India, Ireland, Kazakhstan, Kenya, Luxembourg, Singapore, Venezuela, Yemen, and the Republic of Korea, among many others.</data>
