<node id="&quot;2018&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">2018 is a year in the global life expectancy data collection period with recorded measurements across numerous countries and regions. The data shows significant variation in life expectancy values, ranging from 51.60 years (Lesotho) to 84.35 years (Japan). Notable measurements include China at 77.14 years, India at 70.35 years, the USA at 78.63 years, and Switzerland at 83.29 years. Regional aggregates are also documented, with EUR (Europe) recorded at 77.75 years and AFR (Africa) at 63.78 years. The global life expectancy for 2018 was recorded at 72.89 years. Specific country data points include Canada (81.73 years), Australia (83.02 years), France (82.38 years), Italy (82.78 years), Norway (82.44 years), New Zealand (81.76 years), and numerous other nations across Africa, Asia, Europe, and the Americas, reflecting the comprehensive nature of the 2018 life expectancy tracking dataset.</data>
