<node id="&quot;2017&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">2017 is a year in the global life expectancy data collection period with recorded measurements across numerous countries and regions. The data shows significant variation in life expectancy values, ranging from 51.05 years (Lesotho) to 84.26 years (Japan). Notable country-specific measurements include China at 76.95 years, India at 70.06 years, the USA at 78.50 years, Canada at 81.71 years, Australia at 82.68 years, and Switzerland at 83.14 years. Regional aggregates are also documented, with EUR (Europe) recorded at 77.62 years and AFR (Africa) at 63.36 years. The global average life expectancy for 2017 was recorded at 72.68 years. Additional measurements for various nations span from lower values such as Eswatini at 53.81 years and South Sudan at 58.88 years to higher values including Norway at 82.33</data>
