<node id="&quot;2019&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">2019 is a year in the global life expectancy data collection period, representing the twentieth year in multiple tracking sequences. Life expectancy measurements for 2019 vary significantly across countries and regions, reflecting disparities in healthcare and living conditions worldwide.

Specific country measurements include: China (77.31 years), India (70.73 years), Japan (84.47 years), Italy (82.99 years), Switzerland (83.48 years), Spain (83.14 years), Norway (82.66 years), France (82.53 years), Australia (82.64 years), Canada (82.02 years), New Zealand (81.81 years), Iceland (82.47 years), Israel (82.57 years), Finland (81.65 years), Denmark (81.28 years), Sweden (82.71 years), Slovenia (81.29 years), Czechia (79.14 years), Iran (77.78 years, marking a peak in its data series), Türkiye (77.62 years), Tunisia (77.51 years), Sri Lanka (77.45 years), North Macedonia (76.15 years), Barbados (76.04 years), Lithuania (76.25 years), Brunei Darussalam (76.68 years), Saint Lucia (76.12 years), Thailand (76.92 years), Romania (75.46 years), Serbia (75.92 years), Paraguay (75.08 years), Armenia (75.67 years), Belize (74.86 years), Russian Federation (73.22 years), Jamaica (72.24 years), Bangladesh (73.95 years), Guatemala (72.71 years), Democratic People's Republic of Korea (72.31 years), Dominican Republic (73.91 years), Iraq (72.90 years), Pakistan (67.03 years), Myanmar (68.81 years), Philippines (69.43 years), Honduras (71.44 years), Peru (78.29 years), Nicaragua (78.87 years), Panama (78.97 years), and USA (78.74 years).

Lower life expectancy values were recorded in: Lesotho (51.78 years), Eswatini (55.74 years), Somalia (55.21 years), South Sudan (59.00 years), Chad (59.37 years), Mozambique (58.51 years), Guinea (61.13 years), Mali (61.83 years), Democratic Republic of the Congo (61.83 years), Equatorial Guinea (61.38 years), Burkina Faso (62.61 years), Liberia (63.44 years), Haiti (63.66 years), Burundi (64.32 years), Gambia (64.91 years), Côte d'Ivoire (63.48 years), and Senegal (68.76 years).

Regional aggregates include EUR (78.10 years) and AFR (64.17 years). Additional entities with recorded data include Vietnam, Malaysia, Singapore, Kazakhstan, Belarus, Estonia, Latvia, Cuba, Argentina, Bah</data>
